WAKING UP AND GOING TO SLEEP
----------------------------
----------------------------

"I start at nine and it depends.. i don't finish always at the same time"
I wake up: in Italian beocomes literally "i wake up myself" -> "io mi sveglio" I GO TO SLEEP: Io dormo - io vado a dormire
I WAKE UP: in Italian beocomes literally "i wake up myself" -> "io mi sveglio

------------------------------
----> WAYS TO SAY YOU’RE TIRED
------------------------------

tu sei affaticato: you are tired (as of fatigue)
tu sei stanco: you are tired (as in sleepy)
hai sonno: you are tired (as in sleepy. literally: "you have sleep")
I GO TO SLEEP: Io dormo - io vado a dormire
I WAKE UP: in Italian beocomes literally "i wake up myself" -> "io mi sveglio"

